'''William Gordon Cooper''' (April 14, 1913 - August 11, 1998) played [[college football]] at [[Pennsylvania State University|Penn State]]. After college in 1936 he became a [[Fullback (American football)|fullback]] in the [[National Football League]] for the [[Cleveland Rams]], who the played in the [[AFL II|second American Football League]].<ref>http://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/C/CoopBu20.htm Bud Cooper</ref> When the Rams moved into the NFL in 1937, and Cooper went with them. Even though the NFL confederation gave the membership to the same team owner, this NFL franchise officially became a detach entity because only four players of the team joined the NFL that was newly launched. No personnel of the team joined the NFL league. The four players were [[Mike Sebastian]], [[Stan Pincura]], [[Harry Mattos]] and Bud Cooper.<ref>http://www.greatdefense.net/st-louis-rams.html</ref>

